text: Cole Walsh (born 14 June 1995) is an American athlete specializing in Pole Vault. ==Biography== Cole Wash started his vaulting career at Brophy College Prepatory in Phoenix, Arizona. He continued on to University of Oregon where he was selected for the 2014 World Junior Championships in Athletics. He finished third at 2018 US outdoor Championships, with his personal best of 5.75 m. He finished second at 2019 US outdoor Championships with another jump of 5.76 m. His personal best (indoor) is 5.83 m in Zurich, Switzerland. In 2020 he was given a three-month ban for breaking anti-doping regulations after testing positive for cannabis.
